Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.42,0:00:24.24,Sign,,0,0,110,,{\fade(500,500)\c&H0000E0&\bord0.1\blur0.6\shad4\fs40}Rainbow Across the Pacific Ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.99,0:00:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beautiful this morning too! \NThe sea breeze is so pleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.70,0:00:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do this while taking a deep breath \Nand you'll feel the most refreshed!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.84,0:00:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can really feel that \Nthere's more land beyond the horizon. {nc what she means tbh; 水平線の向こうが膨らんでいくみたい}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.12,0:00:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to like the sea a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.74,0:00:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.46,0:00:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A rainbow bridge, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.90,0:00:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.60,0:00:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad used to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.70,0:00:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"To let people from various countries \Ntravel freely across the Pacific Ocean,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.49,0:00:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,it'd be nice if we could throw \Na couple of light and rainbow bridges over it."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.61,0:00:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the name of the Pacific Ocean \Nmeans "an ocean of peace," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.08,0:01:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.43,0:01:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.90,0:01:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Shuu Gyokuren. {周 玉蓮}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.24,0:01:10.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE0E6DD&\b0\3c&H253011&\fade(0,300)\pos(176.85,18.67)\fs30}Shuu Gyokuren {周 玉蓮}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.12,0:01:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Though her mother is Japanese,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.59,0:01:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,she was born in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.25,0:01:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, her whole family \Nhas come to Japan for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.86,0:01:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, her birthplace is China. {actually "nationality is china" but I need to tie this up with the next line}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.60,0:01:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is our closest neighbor just across the sea, \Nand a fellow Asian country, equal to ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.12,0:01:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mother has been teaching her Japanese \Nfor all her life, so don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.38,0:01:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll become talkative in no time, \Nonce you make friends with her. {act. "she'll become able to talk"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.01,0:01:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it sound good? Let's all get along \Nand help Gyokuren feel at home. {/cooperate w/ ... - whatever that means}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.38,0:01:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Okay!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.38,0:01:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.53,0:01:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! {no clue what he says}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.17,0:01:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to be brave too, Gyokuren.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.01,0:01:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, cheer up and greet everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.06,0:01:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is... S-Shuu Gyokuren.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.10,0:02:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.83,0:02:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,My name
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is K-Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.79,0:02:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Pfeashed to meeth you!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.34,0:02:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? A girl from China?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.39,0:02:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! China is where the pandas come from.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.12,0:02:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody knows that!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.97,0:02:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, Gyokuren \Nmust be having a hard time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.17,0:02:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If Mitsuko shows Gyokuren her affection, \NI'm sure Gyokuren will also like Mitsuko. {/come to like}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.00,0:02:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Two hearts will always find a way \Nto relate to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.09,0:02:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chinese are our closest neighbors, \Nso it'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.41,0:02:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They way you put it is as though \NChina is literally a family next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.67,0:02:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.04,0:02:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Our families, countries, \Nand everything else is the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.12,0:02:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's nothing more important \Nthan for two neighbors to get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.40,0:03:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, you should be kind to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.17,0:03:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.57,0:03:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.65,0:03:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.06,0:03:09.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\u1\c&HCFD1C3&\3c&H3F4423&\b0\fs60\pos(306.99,80.67)}Chinese{\u0}! {中国人}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.07,0:03:10.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HCFD1C3&\3c&H545A34&\b0\fs40}Dirty hands Gyokuren {ワタツ ギョクレン - no clue what watatsu/kutatsu here means, or whatever else it could be; very unlikely it could be watashi}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.07,0:03:11.06,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HCFD1C3&\3c&H4B5031&\b0\fs40\pos(299.65,62.67)}"I c-come from Ch-China..." {わたし中国人あるゆ - no clue what;s aruyu here, assumed they're mocking her introducing herself}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,G-Gyokuren!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.87,0:03:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How could you! {g}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.95,0:03:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Got a problem with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.41,0:03:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh! Mitsuko can't mind her own business! {lit: ... is intrusive person​}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.41,0:03:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Away, you cocky broad! {lit: retreat, this is insolent}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.43,0:03:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hah! Becoming friends with {\i1}me{\i0}? In your dreams! {}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.19,0:03:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.80,0:03:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your problem?!{/got a problem with me}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! The teacher is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.21,0:03:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear Hoshun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.22,0:03:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to Japan, my mom's birthplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I started going to a Japanese school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.81,0:03:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, for some reason, \NI just can't get along with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.46,0:03:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoshun, I can't find another friend like you.{}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.05,0:04:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese teachers are all very good people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.09,0:04:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, if I have enough courage, \NI can make lots of friends in Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.51,0:04:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, what can I do to have more courage?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.56,0:04:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoshun, I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.77,0:04:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Gyokuren.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.03,0:04:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Gyokuren!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.13,0:04:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Gyokuren!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.29,0:04:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Gyokuren!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.67,0:04:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,E-Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.91,0:04:36.91,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HCFD1C3&\3c&H343B1D&\b0\fs40\pos(331.76,30.5)}"My Treasure" {私の宝物}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.48,0:04:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, that's it for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, the weather will be \Nreally nice and warm for our next class meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.76,0:04:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's meet on the green hill \Nunder the lighthouse in the afternoon. {several days later}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.99,0:04:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme would be "My Treasure."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.64,0:04:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick the one thing you value the most \Nand bring it along, so as to introduce it to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.09,0:04:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.81,0:05:01.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H000200&\3c&H9DA284&\b0\fs40\fax0.154894\fscx112.79\fscy107.83\frz-10.6721\frx-6.9416\fry8.0306\xbord2.31\ybord2.16\org(514.29,197.55)\pos(510.79,175.99)}Mitsuko's toys {光湖のオモチャ}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.23,0:05:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.58,0:05:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.78,0:05:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.32,0:05:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You opened your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.33,0:05:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Blonde hair and blue eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.15,0:05:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you're an American doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.24,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you been here for long? {act. more like "you've been in a place like this for eternity?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.99,0:05:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you felt lonely!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.97,0:05:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But you'll be fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.44,0:05:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'll be your friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.81,0:05:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get along well, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.50,0:05:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.99,0:05:55.70,Song,,0,0,0,,A beautiful doll with blue eyes {every line of the song is effectively a guess since I couldn't find the lyrics, no clue what's it to do with celluloid either}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.70,0:06:02.21,Song,,0,0,0,,A celluloid born in America
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.69,0:06:13.76,Song,,0,0,0,,When we arrived to the Japanese port,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.76,0:06:19.64,Song,,0,0,0,,I shed a plenty of bitter tears
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.64,0:06:25.74,Song,,0,0,0,,I can't understand the words they're saying
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.74,0:06:31.59,Song,,0,0,0,,What would I do if I get lost?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.59,0:06:37.55,Song,,0,0,0,,A kind Japanese girl saw me
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.55,0:06:43.47,Song,,0,0,0,,We got along and went to play
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.47,0:06:50.07,Song,,0,0,0,,We got along and went to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.07,0:06:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What a mysterious music box.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.62,0:06:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you, Mitsuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.91,0:07:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a Doll Fairy, the guardian of dolls. {actually just says "I'm a doll fairy in japanese"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.24,0:07:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Doll Fairy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.86,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Although I'm usually invisible to a human eye, \NI let you see me for how kind you've been to Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So this doll's name is Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.16,0:07:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Your kind feelings \Ncan be conveyed to Emily as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.82,0:07:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,There, why won't Emily say something too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.45,0:07:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.53,0:07:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you listen really carefully, \Nyou could hear it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.78,0:07:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Becoming friends with someone always begins \Nwith listening to them quietly and intently.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.86,0:07:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mitsuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! This doll Emily just spoke to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.95,0:07:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been here all alone for a long, long time. \NSo I was unbelievably happy when you showed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.86,0:07:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,A long time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.95,0:08:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"Right. She's been here since before the time \Nyour mom and dad were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Since {\i1}that{\i0} long ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.16,0:08:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When I came to Japan from America,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.98,0:08:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it was 1927. Second year of Showa.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.09,0:08:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That was over 60 years ago from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.99,0:08:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We fostered a hope that the children of America \Nand Japan would live in an eternal harmony,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.51,0:08:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,bound together by the feeling of warm friendship. {/passionate/ardor}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.76,0:08:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 12,000 dolls were donated by Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.21,0:08:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent them across the Pacific, \Nthe ocean of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.67,0:08:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We welcomed the blue-eyed dolls with open arms, \Nas the envoys of peace and friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.65,0:08:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Distributed to elementary schools \Nand kindergartens all over Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.16,0:08:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the dolls were highly treasured by the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.89,0:08:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was one of those 12,000 dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.15,0:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So you were a doll of friendship?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.16,0:09:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, how did you end up in a place like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.70,0:09:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sadly, Japan started a war \Nwith my homeland of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.61,0:09:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,War?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.40,0:09:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,1941. 16th year of Showa, December.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.46,0:09:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Pacific War began.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.13,0:09:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,By then, Japan was already \Nwaging a prolonged war against China.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.82,0:09:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,From that day on, our fates took a drastic turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.39,0:09:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A thing more tragic is hardly imaginable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.41,0:09:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue-eyed dolls were made \Ninto scapegoats for all Americans.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.46,0:09:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They were torn apart, they were burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.36,0:09:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people I met in Japan \Nwere kind and well-meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.50,0:09:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.57,0:09:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,why would they go to war to take each other's lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.89,0:09:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's... That's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.86,0:10:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dolls didn't do anything to deserve this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.57,0:10:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't anyone stop them? {}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.77,0:10:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But Emily...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.46,0:10:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How come you were saved?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.72,0:10:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.32,0:10:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what the world looked like during the war. {lit: I ended up coming to the world during the war}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.22,0:10:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.54,0:10:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.50,0:10:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, according to the principal's advice, \Nwe're chastising Emily today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.80,0:10:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chastising Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.55,0:10:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you staring to the sides? \NYou're doing it too. Go now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.40,0:10:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have a go first!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.92,0:10:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.39,0:11:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.79,0:11:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.40,0:11:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I was truly happy when you found me. {lit is "when mitsuko came" so could be either "when you came here" or "when you stepped up to protect me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.24,0:11:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.23,0:11:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.15,0:11:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.39,0:11:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Traitor! Coward! {unpatriotic person; traitor (to one's country)}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.76,0:11:31.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Please! Not Emily. \NDon't hurt Emily, the doll!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.76,0:11:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily isn't guilty of anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.25,0:11:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I also had a bad feeling about doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.48,0:11:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But thanks to you, I regained my courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.36,0:11:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make sure to protect Emily until a day comes \Nwhen we get to live in peace again, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.09,0:11:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This doll of friendship \Nbetween Japan and America.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.02,0:11:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.16,0:12:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you glad, Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.63,0:12:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.17,0:12:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That music box again...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.51,0:12:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.78,0:12:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You did well, Mitsuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.95,0:12:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Doll Fairy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.74,0:12:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that moment, your courage chose \Nto live in a bright and wonderful future.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.65,0:12:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.33,0:12:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,People encounter all sorts of challenges daily, \Nsometimes getting lost as to how to handle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.56,0:12:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like there are two paths to choose from \Nwhen standing on a split. {lit: in every journey, there are two paths}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.84,0:12:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can only decide for yourself, \Nwhich one to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.56,0:12:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Two paths?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.17,0:12:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,One is the path of cowardice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.10,0:12:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Path of cowardice?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.25,0:12:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the other is the path of courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.07,0:12:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Path of courage?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.27,0:12:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The path of cowardice and the path of courage - \Ndepending on which of these two paths you choose,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.97,0:12:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your future will also change accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.39,0:13:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, you chose the path of courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Emily is currently happy, \Nresting in your embrace.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.37,0:13:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But just now, the kid that looked like Kenta \Nyelled "coward" at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.76,0:13:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, do you suppose the path of courage \Nis to stab the doll with a bamboo spear?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.75,0:13:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.02,0:13:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But Kenta is pretty strong, \Ngood with the horizontal bar and is always lively.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.13,0:13:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I've ever seen him sulking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.26,0:13:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.57,0:13:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.23,0:13:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When his mother died and Kenta was left all alone with his father, he's been feeling very lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.80,0:13:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, because he didn't want anyone to find out,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.13,0:13:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he started putting on intimidating airs \Nand bullying others all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.53,0:13:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you do that, \Nyou can hardly ever make any friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.48,0:13:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Such is the future of those who choose \Nthe path of cowardice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.31,0:14:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a road that only leads up to a dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.54,0:14:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So giving in to your own weak spirit is a no-go?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.67,0:14:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.10,0:14:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, the path of courage \Nmay be painful at first, {unsure what she means by "that time"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.17,0:14:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but the further you advance on it, \Nthe wider and clearer the road becomes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.30,0:14:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I should tell Kenta...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.30,0:14:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! I should tell Gyokuren too, that in order to make some true friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.53,0:14:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll have to take the path of courage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.71,0:14:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, grandma. \NWar is truly scary thing, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.67,0:14:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, Mitsuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.45,0:14:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish everyone in the world would learn to be as honest as Emily's clear blue eyes, {世界中のみんながこのエミリーの澄んだ瞳のように子供の頃の優しい気持ちや友達を大切にする心をずっと変わらずに持ち続けられたらね - I don't really see what's emily's eyes to do with this, kinda weird allegory}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.03,0:14:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to carry on through their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,with the unfaltering spirit of being kind and appreciative towards your friends, like they did as children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.66,0:14:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If everyone did that, we'd never have \Nto live through that senseless war, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.20,0:14:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,A spirit of being appreciative towards your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.02,0:15:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, I'll be sure to become \Ntrue friends with Gyokuren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.50,0:15:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This concludes the story \Nof the blue-eyed doll Emily and the Doll Fairy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.38,0:15:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha! A guardian of dolls, seriously? \NIsn't it just some dream you had?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.34,0:15:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, next is Gyokuren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.27,0:15:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, it's Gyokuren's turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.33,0:15:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you have in that bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.07,0:15:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, show it to us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.10,0:15:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Gyokuren?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.44,0:15:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up, Gyokuren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.79,0:15:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's so irritating!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.39,0:15:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Mitsuko, let others have their turn now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.33,0:15:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave that wimp alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.80,0:15:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Wimp?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.83,0:15:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That there, ain't she a wimp?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.03,0:15:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What now? \NYou got a problem with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.79,0:16:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, please. Let us see your treasure, Gyokuren.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.78,0:16:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We would all like to become true friends with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.75,0:16:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,True friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.78,0:16:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we want to hear your story, \Nfrom start to end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.56,0:16:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all excited to hear \Nsome wonderful stories about China.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.78,0:16:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily, what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.44,0:16:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What could I do to get Gyokuren to open up? {/answer}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.72,0:16:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something for Emily. {no clue what she means - エミリーになら(n)}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.80,0:16:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.86,0:16:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.71,0:16:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.10,0:17:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.44,0:17:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful Chinese doll!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.94,0:17:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I had a doll like that too!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.20,0:17:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So we got a Chinese and an American doll here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.69,0:17:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's getting pretty global! {/worldwide}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Emily, nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.70,0:17:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Hoshun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.48,0:17:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My Chinese fri... Fr...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.88,0:17:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.88,0:17:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Right! My Chinese friend has the same name as her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.78,0:17:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, Hoshun is very good at dancing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.92,0:17:51.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fade(800,1300)}Hoshun {*春 - nc what's first character, prolly something in chinese so w/e}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.40,0:17:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoshun and I have always been friends \Never since we were little. {talking about person here}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.73,0:18:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a bright and cheerful girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.19,0:18:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When it was time for me to leave for Japan, \Nshe gave me this doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.62,0:18:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoshun said she didn't want me to forget her, \Nthat's why the doll's name is also Hoshun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.17,0:18:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a wonderful story, Gyokuren.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.91,0:18:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get along, shall we, Hoshun?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.37,0:18:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.48,0:18:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad for you, Hoshun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.50,0:18:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoshun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.80,0:18:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoshun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.14,0:18:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out, Gyokuren! \NIt's dangerous over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.27,0:18:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoshun! Hoshun, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.72,0:19:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Gyokuren!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It got stuck so high up...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.24,0:19:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we really get it back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.03,0:19:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No chance. That was awfully unlucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.84,0:19:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Give up on it. \NI can fix you up with an even better ribbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.87,0:19:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizue!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.41,0:19:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That ribbon is a proof of my friendship with Hoshun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.30,0:19:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't have that ribbon, \NI don't have Hoshun!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.07,0:19:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a token of warm friendship \Nbetween Gyokuren and Hoshun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.04,0:19:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's quite a pickle...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.80,0:19:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenta.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.74,0:19:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Go get the ribbon.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.49,0:19:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,M-Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.23,0:19:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a ribbon of Gyokuren's precious friendship.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.37,0:19:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. I know you're the only one who can get it, Kenta.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.61,0:20:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay... H-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.54,0:20:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.56,0:20:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No way we're losing that ribbon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.62,0:20:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't afford losing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.73,0:20:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.42,0:20:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Once more!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.74,0:20:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.81,0:20:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsk! I can't reach that branch!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.20,0:20:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenta, use my back to jump to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.56,0:21:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You there, don't just stand idly! \NHelp me push Kenta up from the sides!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.97,0:21:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... Okay. {nc what's second word, prolly not a word at all}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.10,0:21:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jump in two steps, using both me and Yuzuru!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.92,0:21:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,A-Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.84,0:21:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry! Hurry up now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.83,0:21:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.31,0:21:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.13,0:21:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.24,0:21:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.44,0:21:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up, Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.25,0:21:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.91,0:21:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.50,0:21:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Please keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.15,0:21:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.16,0:21:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now comes the most difficult part.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.52,0:21:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We believe in you, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.94,0:21:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.09,0:21:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.47,0:21:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.60,0:21:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Kenta! Thank you for trying, but please stop now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.45,0:21:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is enough! \NPlease get down, it's getting dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.66,0:21:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Geez, you're noisy! \NI'm doing this for myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.61,0:22:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a problem with that?\NKeep that to yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.57,0:22:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.75,0:22:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, Kenta is not struggling \Nfor the twig of camellia, nor for the ribbon. {今ケンタ君が挑んでいるのはヤブツバキの枝でもリボンでもなく }
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.55,0:22:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, Kenta is fighting \Nto take his own path of courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.87,0:22:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's raining!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.63,0:22:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, I need your handkerchiefs!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.22,0:22:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Handkerchiefs?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.36,0:22:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Tie together all the handkerchiefs you have. Quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.25,0:22:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do with our handkerchiefs?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.09,0:22:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No questions, just do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.10,0:22:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.84,0:22:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, give me your handkerchiefs!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.86,0:22:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster! Next strong gust will totally blow it away!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.57,0:22:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick, quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.56,0:22:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Tie them good!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.12,0:22:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.58,0:22:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Faster! You can do it faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.01,0:22:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please use this too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.88,0:22:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mizue.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.26,0:22:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost there, Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.44,0:23:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.29,0:23:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's finished, Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.25,0:23:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, don't drop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.31,0:23:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There, let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.14,0:23:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! So pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.89,0:23:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I got it. \NHere, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.93,0:23:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like a line of flags! {https://jisho.org/word/%E4%B8%87%E5%9B%BD%E6%97%97 - I don't think the english has a word for it or even a concise way to explain it}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.41,0:23:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When you look at this line of handkerchiefs flags, \Nit feels like the whole world is holding hands! {unsure why she says "the handkerchiefs of bankokki"}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.94,0:23:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't make it with the first try, \Nthe ribbon will be blown away!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.95,0:24:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.99,0:24:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it, Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.44,0:24:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.26,0:24:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.26,0:24:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.92,0:24:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it, Kenta!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.28,0:24:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way. That's the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.42,0:24:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.15,0:24:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.53,0:24:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray! He did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.91,0:25:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our Boss!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.72,0:25:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy as that!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.56,0:25:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoshun. My Hoshun!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.55,0:25:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you glad? All your friends in Japan \Nturned out to be such caring people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.54,0:25:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I should've gotten along with them sooner. {no clue what she means: 私元々仲良しになるね - could be "and I was your friend all along" but makes just as little sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.06,0:25:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give us all that nonsense!{}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.53,0:25:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Better tie it good this time, you hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.60,0:25:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Kenta. And thank you once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.65,0:25:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you I wasn't doing it for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.40,0:25:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But you brought Hoshun her ribbon back.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.88,0:25:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a very good person.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.44,0:25:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not complaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.01,0:25:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.46,0:25:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?{}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.60,0:25:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, if you don't mind, may I tell you a bit more?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.24,0:25:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.49,0:26:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I annoyed my mom by saying \NI don't want to go to school this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.63,0:26:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since I came to Japan, I hated going to school, \Nbecause it was so painful day after day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.82,0:26:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, I was scared that I'd be laughed at \Nfor bringing along my precious Hoshun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.65,0:26:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, mom reassured me. {/told me this}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.73,0:26:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,She said I should be proud
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.10,0:26:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of being born and raised in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.25,0:26:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And mom was right!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.60,0:26:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm truly happy to be here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.39,0:26:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,After Kenta brought Hoshun's ribbon back, \Nwith everyone in the class assisting him,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.72,0:26:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see that everyone here is already my friend, \Nsame as Hoshun, back in China.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.55,0:26:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,When Hoshun back in China hears \Nabout what happened today, she'll be... She'll be...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.27,0:26:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So very happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.34,0:27:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A rainbow!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.65,0:27:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And a big one!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.01,0:27:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.16,0:27:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A rainbow bridge stretched across the Pacific Ocean!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.23,0:27:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What colors are there in the rainbow?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.66,0:27:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Red!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.56,0:27:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Orange!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.37,0:27:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yellow!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.46,0:27:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.31,0:27:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Green!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.31,0:27:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's just like everyone says.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.48,0:27:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Without getting together different colors, \Nyou can't build a bridge of light, a rainbow bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.86,0:27:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.13,0:27:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This bridge wouldn't be quite as pretty \Nif it was all one color.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.14,0:27:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Green and purple, and all the other colors \Nare wonderful, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.08,0:27:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.53,0:27:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people, whoever they might be, \Nhave in them one of the beautiful colors. {unsure what to make of saiko here: 人間だって、どんな人でも、最高に素敵な色を持っているの。}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.31,0:27:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no ranking them. {/order}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.81,0:27:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Each and every person is equally #1.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.13,0:27:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, let us all mutually cherish people, \Nwho shine in colors different from our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.64,0:27:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, which color would I be?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.17,0:27:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.37,0:28:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.41,0:28:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.12,0:28:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Those dolls
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.25,0:28:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,were the dolls that crossed the Pacific Ocean \Ntogether with Emily, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.34,0:28:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,On the rainbow of friendship, \Nover the ocean of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.93,0:28:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's our turn to stretch this rainbow \Nall across the globe and cross it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.48,0:28:56.95,Song,,0,0,0,,Friends of hope across the sea, {海の向こうの　希望の友よ　}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.95,0:29:03.61,Song,,0,0,0,,If you stay still and close your eyes, you'll feel {静かにじっと　目を閉じれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.61,0:29:10.09,Song,,0,0,0,,A vast ocean spreading though your eyelids {瞼に広がる　大海原　}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.09,0:29:17.63,Song,,0,0,0,,And a gentle sea breeze caressing your back {そよ風いっぱい　背に受けて}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.77,0:29:25.36,Song,,0,0,0,,Walk upon the path of courage \NWalk upon the path of courage {勇気の道を進もうよ　}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.36,0:29:31.92,Song,,0,0,0,,Now, let's stretch a rainbow across the Pacific Ocean! {さあ　かけよう虹を　太平洋に}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.92,0:29:38.49,Song,,0,0,0,,Walk upon the path of courage \NWalk upon the path of courage {勇気の道を進もうよ　}
